ee a letter every year to remind you how much must be paid and when.</p>\n\n<h2>Deductions for administrative costs</h2>\n\n<p>You can take up to £1 towards administrative costs for each deduction, on top of the amount of the <abbr title=\"deduction from earnings order\">DEO</abbr>. You can take it even if it reduces your employee&rsquo;s income below the <a href=\"/make-child-maintenance-deductions-employee-pay/how-deduction-from-earnings-orders-work\" title=\"protected earnings proportion or protected earnings rate\">protected earnings proportion or protected earnings rate</a>.</p>\n\n<h2>Informing your employee</h2>\n\n<p>You must inform your employee in writing about each deduction when they are given their pay statement. Include the amount (if any) you deduct towards your expenses.</p>\n\n<p>If pay statements are not usually given, you should inform your employee in writing. You should do this no later than the employee’s pay day after the deduction was made.</p>\n\n<h2>If you pay the wrong amount</h2>\n\n<p>If you find a mistake in the amount you&rsquo;ve paid, contact the <abbr title=\"Child Support Agency\">CSA</abbr>.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Child Support Agency employer helpline</strong><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0845 713 6010<br />\n<strong>Textphone:</strong> 0845 713 8924</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/make-child-maintenance-deductions-employee-pay/change-of-circumstances","slug":"change-of-circumstances","order":6,"title":"Change of circumstances","body":"<p>If your employee’s circumstances change, phone the Child Support Agency (<abbr title=\"Child Support Agency\">CSA</abbr>) employer helpline.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Child Support Agency employer helpline</strong><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0845 713 6010<br />\n<strong>Textphone:</strong> 0845 713 8924</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>If your business stops trading, or if your employee leaves your employment, you must tell the <abbr title=\"Child Support Agency\">CSA</abbr> in writing within 10 days.</p>\n\n<p>You should also tell the <abbr title=\"Child Support Agency\">CSA</abbr> if your employee changes their hours.</p>\n\n<p>The <abbr title=\"Child Support Agency\">CSA</abbr> will send you and your employee a revised deduction from earnings order (<abbr title=\"deduction from earnings order\">DEO</abbr>).</p>\n\n<h2>If the <abbr title=\"Child Support Agency\">CSA</abbr> cancels a <abbr title=\"deduction from earnings order\">DEO</abbr></h2>\n\n<p>The <abbr title=\"Child Support Agency\">CSA</abbr> will write to you and your employee to tell you the <abbr title=\"deduction from earnings order\">DEO</abbr> has been cancelled. It will ask you to stop taking deductions from the date of the letter.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>You must only stop taking deductions if the <abbr title=\"Child Support Agency\">CSA</abbr> tells you <strong>in writing</strong>.</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/make-child-maintenance-deductions-employee-pay/if-you-dont-help-the-csa","slug":"if-you-dont-help-the-csa","order":7,"title":"If you don't help the CSA","body":"<p>It’s an offence to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>not provide information when it’s required</li>\n  <li>make a false statement or representation </li>\n  <li>knowingly provide false information</li>\n  <li>delay or obstruct an inspector on purpose</li>\n  <li>refuse or fail to answer any questions or supply any information or to produce any document when it’s asked for </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The Child Support Agency (<abbr title=\"Child Support Agency\">CSA</abbr>) sometimes sends inspectors to interview paying parents at work. You must let them interview your employee. </p>\n\n<p>The &lsquo;paying parent&rsquo; is the parent the child doesn&rsquo;t live with.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>If you’re found guilty of any of these offences you can be fined up to £1,000.</p>\n</div>\n\n"}]},"updated_at":"2