f the accommodation is optional, it only counts as a cost if the worker uses it.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>Social housing providers</h3>\n\n<p>If someone working for a social housing provider gets accommodation from their work, this doesn&rsquo;t automatically count towards the minimum wage.</p>\n\n<p>It only counts if the accommodation is linked to the employment. For example, a care warden who has to live on site has their accommodation linked to their job.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>It doesn’t matter if the cost of the accommodation is taken from the workers’ wages beforehand or if the worker pays the cost after they’ve received their wages.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Higher or further education institutions</h2>\n\n<p>Accommodation isn&rsquo;t counted when working out the minimum wage if it&rsquo;s provided by a higher or further education institution to a worker who is enrolled on a full-time course with the institution.</p>\n"},"updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:19:26+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Your pay, tax and the National Minimum Wage","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working%2Ftax-minimum-wage.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes National Minimum Wage rates, keeping pay records and pay rights","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working%2Ftax-minimum-wage","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working/tax-minimum-wage"},"parent":{"title":"Working, jobs and pensions","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes holidays and finding a job","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Payroll","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people%2Fpayroll.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Paying HMRC, employee expenses and benefits and paying staff","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://ww