>\n\n<p>There are 4 ways you can get shares under <abbr title=\"Share Incentive Plans\">SIPs</abbr>.</p>\n\n<h2>Free shares</h2>\n\n<p>Your employer can give you up to £3,000 of free shares in any tax year. </p>\n\n<h2>Partnership shares</h2>\n\n<p>You can buy shares out of your salary before tax deductions. There&rsquo;s a limit to how much you can spend - either £1,500 or 10% of your income for the tax year, whichever is lower.</p>\n\n<h2>Matching shares</h2>\n\n<p>Your employer can give you up to 2 free matching shares for each partnership share you buy.</p>\n\n<h2>Dividend shares</h2>\n\n<p>If you get dividends from free, partnership or matching shares:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you can use them to buy more shares</li>\n  <li>you won&rsquo;t pay Income Tax if you keep the dividend shares for at least 3 years</li>\n  <li>you can invest up to £1,500 of dividends each tax year in this way</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>If you take shares out of a <abbr title=\"Share Incentive Plan\">SIP</abbr> early, you’ll have to pay Income Tax and National Insurance on them.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>There&rsquo;s detailed information on <abbr title=\"Share Incentive Plans\">SIPs</abbr> in a guide from HM Revenue &amp; Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>).</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/shareschemes/sip-info-employees.rtf\" title=\"Download 'A guide to SIPs' (RTF, 82KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘A guide to <abbr title=\"Share Incentive Plans\">SIPs</abbr>’ (RTF, 82KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/tax-employee-share-schemes/save-as-you-earn-saye","slug":"save-as-you-earn-saye","order":3,"title":"Save As You Earn (SAYE)","body":"<p>This is a savings-related share scheme where you can buy shares with your savings for a fixed price.</p>\n\n<p>You can save up to £250 a month under the scheme. At the end of your savings contract (3, 5 or 7 years) you can use the savings 