ead teacher of a maintained school on behalf of the local education authority</li>\n  <li>the work is being paid for by a charity or trust</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You can only get permission to exempt payments less than £1,000 if you&rsquo;re a contractor spending more than £1 million a year on average. To get permission, call the <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> helpline:</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong><abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> helpline</strong><br />\n0845 366 7899<br />\n8am to 8pm, Monday to Friday<br />\n8am to 4pm, Saturday</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>There are no exemptions for subcontractors, and private householders are never treated as <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> contractors - regardless of how much they spend.</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/what-is-the-construction-industry-scheme/if-your-business-is-based-outside-the-uk","slug":"if-your-business-is-based-outside-the-uk","order":4,"title":"If your business is based outside the UK","body":"<p>The Construction Industry Scheme (<abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr>) covers almost all types of construction work done in the UK. It doesn&rsquo;t matter if your business is based in the UK or not.</p>\n\n<p>HM Revenue &amp; Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>) classes you a &lsquo;non-resident business&rsquo; if you&rsquo;re based outside the UK. No matter where you&rsquo;re based, <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> still applies if you&rsquo;re:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a contractor who pays subcontractors for construction work they do in the UK</li>\n  <li>a subcontractor who gets paid by contractors for doing construction work in the UK</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>This means that if you’re a non-resident business you have to follow the same <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> rules as UK-based <a href=\"/what-you-must-do-as-a-cis-contractor/register-with-cis\" title=\"what you must do as a CIS contractor\">contractors</a> and <a href=\"/what-you-must-do-as-a-cis-subcontractor/register-with-cis\" title=\"what you must do as a CIS subcontractor\">subcontractors</a>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>It doesn&rsquo;t matter where payment is made - it&rsquo;s just down to the work you&rsquo;re doing and whether it&rsquo;s covered by <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr>.</p>\n\n<p>There&rsquo;s a full list of types of construction work included and excluded from <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> in the <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> guide for contractors and subcontractors.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/forms/cis340.pdf\" title=\"Download 'CIS guide for contractors and subcontractors' (PDF, 267KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘<abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> guide for contractors and subcontractors’ (PDF, 267KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>How to register</h2>\n\n<p>You must register before any work starts. Register by contacting the <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> Charity, Assets and Residence (<abbr title=\"Charity, Assets and Residence\">CAR</abbr>) - <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> team. </p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> <abbr title=\"Charity, Assets and Residence\">CAR</abbr> <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> team</strong><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0151 472 6273<br />\n<strong>If calling from outside UK:</strong> + 44 151 472 6273</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Or you can write to:</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\n<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> <abbr title=\"Charity, Assets and Residence\">CAR</abbr>  \n<br />Personal Tax Internati