Your contractor will make <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> deductions from the payments they make to you. These count towards your tax and National Insurance payments when you fill in your Self Assessment tax return.</p>\n\n<p>Once you&rsquo;ve registered with the <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr>, you can apply for <a href=\"/what-you-must-do-as-a-cis-subcontractor/how-to-get-gross-payment-status\" title=\"How to get gross payment status\">gross payment status</a> if your business passes some tests. This is where you get your full payment without any deductions being made (you take care of these yourself).</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If you’re based abroad but do construction work in the UK you still need to register with <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr>, but the <a href=\"/what-is-the-construction-industry-scheme/if-your-business-is-based-outside-the-uk\" title=\"Registration if you're based outside the UK\">registration process</a> is different.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>If your business is a limited company</h2>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re a company subcontractor and you&rsquo;ve had <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> deductions taken from your payments, you&rsquo;ll need to complete a <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/paye/payroll/year-end/annual-return.htm\" title=\"P35 Employer Annual Return\">P35 Employer Annual Return</a> - usually online.</p>\n\n<p>You can use the P35 to reclaim deductions taken from the payments - there&rsquo;s more information about this on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/cis/sub/p35return.htm\" title=\"HMRC website - P35 returns\"><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> website.</a></p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/what-you-must-do-as-a-cis-subcontractor/how-to-get-gross-payment-status","slug":"how-to-get-gross-payment-status","order":2,"title":"How to get gross payment status","body":"<p>When you&rsquo;ve registered with the Construction Industry Scheme (<abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr>), you can apply for gross payment status if your business passes some tests.</p>\n\n<p>This means your contractor pays your full payments. You take care of your own tax and National Insurance instead of having deductions made from your payments by your\ncontractor.</p>\n\n<p>To qualify, you must show HM Revenue and Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>) that your business passes 3 tests.</p>\n\n<h2>Business test</h2>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll need to show that your business:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>does construction work (or provides labour for it) in the UK</li>\n  <li>is run through a bank account </li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Turnover test</h2>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> will look at your turnover for the last 12 months. Ignoring <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> and the cost of materials, your turnover must be at least:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>£30,000 if you&rsquo;re a sole trader</li>\n  <li>£30,000 for each partner in a partnership, or at least £200,000 for the whole partnership</li>\n  <li>£30,000 for each director of a company, or at least £200,000 for the whole company</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If your company’s controlled by 5 people or fewer, you must have an annual turnover of £30,000 for each of them.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Compliance test</h2>\n\n<p>You must have kept up to date with your tax and National Insurance in the past. You&rsquo;re allowed a few lapses - full details are on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/cis/subcontractors/advice-pay.htm#2\" title=\"HMRC website\"><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> website.</a></p>\n\n<p>Once you&rsquo;re registered you must declare your payments in your Self Assessment tax return at the end of the tax year.  </p>\n\n<p>Apply by calling the <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> helpline:</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong><abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> helpline</strong><br />\n0845 366 7899 \nMonday to Friday, 8am to 8pm<br />\nSaturday, 8am to 4pm</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Keeping your gross payment status</h2>\n\n<p>Make sure you&rsquo;re not late with your Self Assessment tax returns and <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> payments - you could lose gross payment status otherwise.</p>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> checks on this once a year with a review called a <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/cis/subcontractors/gross-paid-review.htm\" title=\"Tax Treatment Qualification Test (TTQT)\">Tax Treatment Qualification Test (<abbr title=\"Tax Treatment Qualification Test\">TTQT</abbr>).</a></p>\n\n<p>If you fail the review, you&rsquo;ll get a letter explaining why you’ve lost your status and how you can appeal. Usually you’ll have 90 days from the date of the letter.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/what-you-must-do-as-a-cis-subcontractor/making-changes-to-your-business-status","slug":"making-changes-to-your-business-status","order":3,"title":"Making changes to your business status","body":"<p>Significant changes to your business can impact on your Construction Industry Scheme (<abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr>) registration. If you have <a href=\"how-to-get-gross-payment-status\" title=\"How to get gross payment status\">gross payment status</a>, you may need to apply again. </p>\n\n<h2>Changes you must report</h2>\n\n<p>Tell HM Revenue &amp; Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>) if you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>change from a sole trader to a partnership</li>\n  <li>become a sole trader after a partnership breaks up </li>\n  <li>create a company</li>\n  <li>add new shareholders</li>\n  <li>stop trading  </li>\n  <li>change your business, residential or registered address</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>There’s detailed advice about changes you must report on the <a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/cis/subcontractors/changes.htm\" title=\"HMRC website\" rel=\"external\"><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> website.</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Report changes by calling the <abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> helpline:</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong><abbr title=\"Construction Industry Scheme\">CIS</abbr> helpline</strong><br />\n0845 366 7899 <br />\nMonday to Friday, 8am to 8pm<br />\nSaturday, 8am to 4pm</p>\n</div>\n\n"}]},"updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:25:37+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Payroll","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people%2Fpayroll.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Paying HMRC, employee expenses and benefits and paying staff","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people%2Fpayroll","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people/payroll"},"parent":{"title":"Employing people","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes pay, contracts and hiring","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Your pay, tax and the National Minimum Wage","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working%2Ftax-minimum-wage.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes National Minimum Wage rates, keeping pay records and pay rights","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working%2Ftax-minimum-wage","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working/tax-minimum-wage"},"parent":{"title":"Working, jobs and pensions","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes holidays and finding a job","type":"sect